  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Emergency Shelter and NFI Support to IDPs displaced by conflict from Hawiga</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During this four-month initiative, ACTED will procure and pre-position emergency sealing-off kits (ESOKs) and mobile non-food item kits (MNFIs), and distribute them to IDPs fleeing the Hawiga offensive, targeting the Shirqat District, Salah-Al-Din. 

This first line response will promote the safety and dignity of families affected by conflict by ensuring that they have 1) access to shelter conditions which meet minimum standards and 2) access to critical life-saving non-food items. 

This project will use a mobile team approach which will enable a flexible approach that can respond quickly to rapidly changing situations and provide services where gaps exist. 

The proposed activities are part of a mobile intervention which also includes a CCCM team, and referrals to ACTED Child Protection teams will be made wherever necessary. 

The intervention will target 10,500 IDPs living in unfinished living in collective shelters or damaged / unfinished buildings. A total of 1,750 ESOKs and 1,750 MNFIs will be distributed to households, and wherever possible each family will receive each of the kits. The make-up of the kits have been based on technical guidance by the Shelter-NFI cluster and adapted based on the results of post-distribution monitoring results of previous SNFI ACTED projects. The MNFIs provide an effective first line response that can cover the essential NFIs needs of a family of 6 for two weeks, and the ESOKs will ensure households are able to improve their shelters to standards which promotes privacy and dignity, which is protected from the climate and which adheres to minimal standards of health, safety and security.</narrative>
  </description>
